  <div class="image-text-banner--heading">
  







<img src="//web.archive.org/web/20191219074139im_/https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1673/2809/files/WhyItWorks_240x.png?v=1529007217" srcset="//web.archive.org/web/20191219074139im_/https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1673/2809/files/WhyItWorks_50x.png?v=1529007217      50w, //web.archive.org/web/20191219074139im_/https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1673/2809/files/WhyItWorks_160x.png?v=1529007217     160w, //web.archive.org/web/20191219074139im_/https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1673/2809/files/WhyItWorks_240x.png?v=1529007217     240w, //web.archive.org/web/20191219074139im_/https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1673/2809/files/WhyItWorks_480x.png?v=1529007217     480w, //web.archive.org/web/20191219074139im_/https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1673/2809/files/WhyItWorks_600x.png?v=1529007217     600w, //web.archive.org/web/20191219074139im_/https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1673/2809/files/WhyItWorks_840x.png?v=1529007217     840w, //web.archive.org/web/20191219074139im_/https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1673/2809/files/WhyItWorks_960x.png?v=1529007217     960w, //web.archive.org/web/20191219074139im_/https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1673/2809/files/WhyItWorks_1024x.png?v=1529007217     1024w, //web.archive.org/web/20191219074139im_/https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1673/2809/files/WhyItWorks_2048x.png?v=1529007217     2048w" sizes="(min-width: 776px) 45vw, 100vw" alt="Why It Works" class="" data-js-responsive="true"/>

  </div>
  <div class="image-text-banner--copy">
    <p>Our bestseller for a reason, the bloat-fighting blend of organic ginger, cinnamon, turmeric, maqui fruit and a prebiotic works fast to reduce bloating and an uncomfortable stomach. The formula is a combination of soothing anti-inflammatories, traditionally used in Ayurvedic medicine and traditional Chinese medicine, and digestive enzyme triggering ingredients.&nbsp;</p><p>Turmeric is a natural anti-inflammatory and antispasmodic (i.e. helps to ease cramps) with carminative properties. Studies show that daily supplementation of turmeric can be beneficial for IBS symptoms, <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20191219074139/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15673996">helping to relieve bloating and abdominal pain</a>.&nbsp;</p><p>Both Cinnamon and Ginger have been used to treat gastrointestinal issues for thousands of years. Ginger has been proven to decrease <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20191219074139/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3958926/">IBS symptoms up to 57%</a>, and cinnamon is a carminative, an agent that helps break up intestinal gas and trigger digestive enzymes.</p><p>The prebiotic inulin is derived from organic chicory and helps to support the balance of good bacteria in your gut as well as stabilizing your blood sugar levels. It helps to think of prebiotics as a &lsquo;fertilizer&rsquo; in your gut, feeding the good bacteria and creating a diverse environment where they can thrive and multiply.&nbsp;</p><p>Debloat Food works immediately relieve common symptoms of over-indulgence, bloating and IBS. Spicy with a warm kick of ginger, it tastes delicious in oat milk, turmeric lattes, and smoothies.</p><p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20191219074139/https://www.thenueco.com/blogs/journal/why-am-i-always-bloated">How to battle feeling bloated. </a></p>
  </div>
</div>

</div>
  

